Wale Oyewale, Ibadan A former Editor and board chairman of Daily Times, Chief Areoye Oyebola, is dead. Oyebola, a renowned author and publisher, reportedly died in his Oluyole Estate residence in Ibadan, on Monday morning at the age of 84. A prolific writer, Oyebola authored 26 books during his lifetime. He started his journalism career in 1968 and was credited as the pioneer and father of investigative journalism in Nigeria. He edited the Daily Times in the early 70s. Before his journalism career, he was the Head of Department of Economics at the Olivet Height School, Oyo after he had graduated from the University of Ibadan in 1964 with a Bachelor of Science degree in Economics. It was gathered that the deceased attended a meeting of Ibadan Action Council, an affiliate of the Central Council of Ibadan Indigenes, hosted by Chief Niyi Akintola on Sunday. Copyright PUNCH.
